snippet: Egypt's Health Ministry said at least 73 soccer fans were killed, and hundreds more wounded, in clashes that erupted after a match in the city of Port Said.
abstract: Egypt's Health Ministry said at least 73 soccer fans were killed, and hundreds more wounded, in clashes that erupted after a match in the city of Port Said.
lead_paragraph: Updated | 11:46 p.m. As my colleague David Kirkpatrick reports, Egypt's Health Ministry said Wednesday that at least 73 soccer fans were killed, and hundreds more wounded, in clashes that erupted after a match that night in the city of Port Said.

headline.main: Egyptians See Political Overtones in Deadly Soccer Riot
